article.headline: Valparaiso 56, Washington State 60
article.story:
PULLMAN, Wash. (AP) -- Jenna Stangler scored 16 points to lead
Valparaiso past the Washington State Cougars 56-50 at Friel Court
on Tuesday night.

The Crusaders (5-4) won the first ever meeting between the two
schools even though they were out rebounded 45-30.

Valparaiso turned the ball over nine times in the first half but
held on to a four-point lead, 27-23, at halftime. It's ranked third
in the nation in turnovers with 11.4 per game, and finished Tuesday
night with 12 turnovers.

The Cougars (4-5) turned the ball over 20 times.

Senior Emma Joneby brought the Cougars back within two late in
the second half, but junior Jamie Gutowski hit a 3-pointer with
1:12 left in the fourth quarter to put Valparaiso up by five.

Cougar sophomore Kate Benz recorded her third double-double of
the season scoring 21 points and pulling down 15 rebounds.

Valparaiso's Tamra Braun also recorded a double-double with 10
points and 10 rebounds.
